[[[break]]]added at line 0: *lime {code ----
*What's it all about then?*
Something to do with the meta-philosophical aspects of McDowell's Mind and World.  In particular I think  I'll be looking at the way in which it can be compared with Wittgenstein's meta-philosophy.  

Bruin was of the opinion that he has diverged significantly from Witt. both in his use of Rorty's concept of a "picture" and in his attempt to give an historical justification for his meta-philosophical position.
----
*Next Steps*
- Read through the parts of McDowell (including the later lecture series) in which he explicitly refers to his metaphilosophy.
- Read through some of Rorty's stuff (The Mirror of ature in particular) in order to get a feel for his "picture" concept.
----
